<figureCitation id="136E2A17FFCCFFCA04A8AA3EFD57D2F3" box="[689,759,1914,1938]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8. 1" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1672,1695]" captionTargetBox="[166,1390,199,1597]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1648]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. 1 — Anthaxia (Haplanthaxia) antennata sp. nov., holotype, male, 3.5 mm; 2 — A. (H.) auroviolacea sp. nov., holotype, male, 3.1 mm; 3 — A. (H.) onilahyiana sp. nov., holotype, male, 2.5 mm; 4 — A. (H.) antennata sp. nov., aedeagus, holotype; 5 — A. (H.) auroviolacea sp. nov., aedeagus, holotype; 6 — A. (H.) onilahyiana sp. nov., aedeagus, holotype; 7 — A. (H.) auroviolacea sp. nov., right antenna, holotype; 8 — same, right protibia, holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/207444/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number id="3D9D24B5FFCCFFCA04FEAA3EFD57D2F3" box="[743,759,1914,1938]" pageId="1" pageNumber="49" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
); ventral surface black with green lustre, antennae and legs dark golden green; entire body without pubescence except posterior portion of abdominal ventrites with short, very sparse, white pubescence.
</paragraph>
